reviews.text: Awful service from the guy in the ticket office. Asked for info on what train would be best to get and he told me do what you want. very short tempered and the chucked my tickets at me. Looking to put a formal complaint in as I also know of someone else who has had the same problem with his attitude.
OK but like a outer towns it is hit hard by the presence of all the malls
Railway station with direct links to Manchester and Liverpool. Staffed office on the Manchester bound side. Handy for town centre.
Local station linking Urmston to Manchester city centre, Warrington and Liverpool. Handily-placed pub on the platform.

The station office is hardly ever open and when it is, the employee seems to be dis-interested every time. Can be quite confusing when trains are cancelled or delayed due to their being two sides and officials only stay on the side heading to Manchester.
